    "drift_notes": [
      "Brand cyan was tightened in May 2026: #30C5F5 (--cyan), #33C4FF (--cyan-soft), #36B7F6 (--cyan-deep / logo). The earlier palette used #56A6D4 / #8CD2F4 / #2A4DD0 / #8B90DD — an indigo-leaning family that reads as 'older' next to the new cyan.",
      "Body / heading typography moved Roboto -> Geist (body) + GT Pressura Extended (display). The plotting Python/R themes still keep Roboto as the matplotlib/ggplot fallback because GT Pressura is a paid display face we cannot ship inside a figure — Geist is acceptable if installed locally.",
      "The legacy binding-strength palette is preserved verbatim under `legacy_*` keys for figure backwards-compatibility. NEW figures should use the `binding_strength_2026` family below, which uses cyan / white / dim and matches the current brand tokens."
    ]
